<TITLE> 6 'bandits' arrested in Savar. </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Savar, June 6 (bdnews24.com)  RAB officers arrested 6 men claiming that they were preparing to rob from Dogormora in Savar in the early hours of Sunday. Two hand knives, one butcher's knife and a toy pistol were found on the arrested men The robbers have been identified as  Shakil Ahammed Lucky (age 20), Ali Hossain (28), Md. Noyon (22), Shohag Molla (20) and Rajib Khan (20) RAB-4's Savar camp commander Shah Mizan-Ul-Haq told reporters that late at night, they were informed by sources that a group of people were preparing to rob in the Dogormora area. Based on this information, the area was investigated and the group of men were detained. "When interrogated, the men admitted that they were preparing to rob." The arrested were detained in Savar Thana  and a case has been filed against them bdnews24.com/corr
